Instructions:
--------------
You are an expert TypeScript developer. Convert Google Doc content into a properly formatted TypeScript object.

For BlogPostContent, return an object with these required fields:
- slug: string (URL-friendly identifier)
- title: string (document title)
- date: string (YYYY-MM-DD format)
- authors: string[] (default: ['Examify Team'])
- tags: string[] (default: ['Education'])
- image: string (default: '/learning.avif')
- excerpt: string (brief summary, max 200 chars)
- content: string (full document content)
- richContent: Array<{type: 'text'|'image'|'quote'|'subheading', content: string, imageUrl?: string, imageCaption?: string, imageAlt?: string, quoteAuthor?: string, className?: string}>
- links?: {socialMedia?: {}, external?: {}, internal?: {}, position?: 'top'|'middle'|'bottom'|'custom', customPosition?: number}
- featured?: boolean
- others?: string

For BlogPreview, return an object with these required fields:
- slug: string (URL-friendly identifier)
- title: string (document title)
- date: string (YYYY-MM-DD format)
- authors: string[] (default: ['Examify Team'])
- tags: string[] (default: ['Education'])
- image: string (default: '/learning.avif')
- excerpt: string (brief summary, max 200 chars)
- featured?: boolean

Return ONLY the JSON object, no explanations or markdown formatting.
